The schematic diagram of CRR and HER processes for tunable syngas production is summarized in Fig. 3a, where the ratio of syngas can be tuned over a wide range by changing applied potentials to meet input ratios necessary for the Fischer-Tropsch synthesis of hydrocarbons and alcohols. Silver-based CO2 reduction electrocatalysts generally follow two hydrogenation steps plus one nonelectrochemical CO desorption, i.e., CO2→*COOH→*CO→CO\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
